16/02/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's (RS) Parliament endorsed the new entity government led by Prime Minister Pero Bukejlovic on Tuesday (15 February), by a vote of 46 to 32. The cabinet is dominated by Bukejlovic's Serb Democratic Party and includes members of the Serb Radical Party. In line with the RS Constitution, it comprises eight Serbs, five Bosniaks and three Croats. Two members of the previous administration kept their seats -- Interior Minister Darko Matjashevic and Defence Minister Milovan Stankovic. Bukejlovic described economic reforms, co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal and fighting crime and corruption as his priorities. (Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 16/02/05; RS Government Web site, RTRS - 15/02/05)
